{% extends "_base.html.j2" %}

{% block title %}About usbills.ai{% endblock %}

{% block description %}How usbills.ai works and what its metrics mean{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-4xl">
    <header class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-semibold text-gray-800">About this project</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">How we analyze US federal legislation</p>
    </header>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6 sm:p-8 space-y-8">
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Overview</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-justify">
                <p class="mb-2">
                    usbills.ai is an open source project that intends to help the general public understand
                    US Federal legislation.</p>
                <p class="mb-2">
                    You can look at or help improve the source code that created this website on GitHub:<br />
                    <strong><a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/alea-institute/federal-bill-statistics/">https://github.com/alea-institute/federal-bill-statistics/</a></strong>
                </p>

                <p class="font-medium mb-2">
                    The project provides automated analysis of US federal legislation using a combination of
                    traditional natural language processing and large language models.  As such, it might be incomplete,
                    inaccurate, or otherwise inappropriate for you to rely on.  This automated analysis is meant to
                    complement, not replace, your own review of bills. Always read the original bill text and
                    consult qualified legal professionals for legal advice.
                </p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic mb-2">
                    Note: AI-generated content is marked with an <span class="ai-tag">AI</span> tag.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Bulk download from /index.json -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Bulk Data Download</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-justify">
                <p class="mb-2">
                    You can download a complete copy of all metadata, statistics, and generated commentary
                    for all bills in JSON format below.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-2">
                    <a href="/index.json" class="link">Download all bills</a>
                </p>
                <p class="mb-2">
                    This JSON file is updated daily, and while it does not contain the text, Markdown, or HTML rendering
                    of the bills, it does contain links to each bill's complete JSON copy in the `json_url` field.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>


        <!-- Data Collection -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">How We Get Bills</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-justify">
                <p>
                    We retrieve bills directly from the govinfo.gov API, an official source for US federal legislative
                    information operated by the Government Publishing Office (GPO). For each bill:
                </p>
                <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                    <li>We download the official metadata and XML version</li>
                    <li>We parse and extract the bill content, structure, and key information</li>
                    <li>We store this in a standardized format for subsequent analysis</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-2">
                    Bills are updated daily as new versions become available in the govinfo.gov API. We maintain links
                    to the original source documents so you can always verify the information.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Analysis Process -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Our Analysis Process</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-justify">
                <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Traditional NLP Analysis</h3>
                <p>
                    We first analyze bills using traditional natural language processing techniques:
                </p>
                <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                    <li>Tokenization - Breaking text into individual words and punctuation</li>
                    <li>Syntactic parsing and part-of-speech tagging - Identifying nouns, verbs, adjectives, etc.</li>
                    <li>Named entity recognition - Identifying organizations, people, locations, etc.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="font-medium mb-2 mt-4">Large Language Model Analysis</h3>
                <p>
                    We then use state-of-the-art large language models to provide:
                </p>
                <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                    <li>Plain language summaries of bill sections and overall content</li>
                    <li>Key issue identification and analysis</li>
                    <li>ELI5 ("Explain Like I'm 5") descriptions</li>
                    <li>Commentary on potential implications</li>
                    <li>Filter named entities for relevance and importance</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Metrics Guide -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Understanding Our Metrics</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-justify space-y-4">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Basic Metrics</h3>
                    <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                        <li><strong>Sections</strong>: Number of major divisions in the bill</li>
                        <li><strong>Words/Tokens</strong>: Total count of words in the bill</li>
                        <li><strong>Characters</strong>: Total count of characters (excluding whitespace)</li>
                        <li><strong>Sentences</strong>: Total number of sentences</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Language Statistics</h3>
                    <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                        <li><strong>Parts of Speech</strong>: Counts of nouns, verbs, adjectives, etc.</li>
                        <li><strong>Key Phrases</strong>: Important terms and their frequency</li>
                        <li><strong>Entity Counts</strong>: Mentions of organizations, people, places, etc.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Complexity Metrics</h3>
                    <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                        <li>
                            <strong>Average Word Length</strong>: Longer words often indicate more technical content
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <strong>Average Sentence Length</strong>: Longer sentences can indicate more complex ideas
                        </li>
                        <li><strong>Token Entropy</strong>: Measures vocabulary diversity and complexity. Higher values indicate more diverse/complex language.</li>
                        <li>
                            <strong><a class="link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Automated_readability_index" target="_blank">Automated Readability Index (ARI)</a></strong>: Estimates the age or years of education
                            needed to understand the text
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Deciles</h3>
                    <p>
                        Many metrics show a decile ranking (1-10) comparing the bill to other bills:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                        <li><strong>Deciles 1-3</strong>: Lower than typical (green)</li>
                        <li><strong>Deciles 4-7</strong>: Typical range (yellow)</li>
                        <li><strong>Deciles 8-10</strong>: Higher than typical (red)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                        Example: A bill in the 9th decile for token count means it has more words than 
                        about 80-90% of bills.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Important Notes -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Important Notes</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-justify space-y-4">
                <div class="p-4 bg-red-50 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">AI Content Limitations</h3>
                    <p>
                        Content marked with <span class="ai-tag">AI</span> is generated by large language models and:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                        <li>May contain errors or misinterpretations</li>
                        <li>Should not be treated as legal advice</li>
                        <li>Is meant to supplement, not replace, human analysis</li>
                        <li>May reflect biases present in training data</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>The model used to generate each bill's content is displayed in the footer.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="p-4 bg-yellow-50 rounded-lg">
                    <h3 class="font-medium mb-2">Reading Original Sources</h3>
                    <p>
                        We strongly encourage users to:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="mb-2 list-disc list-inside prose text-left">
                        <li>Read the original bill text using the provided govinfo.gov links</li>
                        <li>Verify any important information against official sources</li>
                        <li>Consult qualified legal professionals for legal advice</li>
                        <li>Use our analysis as a starting point for deeper research</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}